Calling Plaid’s `openPlaidIdvLink()` directly inside the `PlaidFormTrigger` render (see `src/pages/OrganizationApplication/FinancialAuthority/AcceptanceForm/PlaidIdentityButton.tsx:36`) causes React to fire updates while it is still rendering, which triggers the warning `unstable_flushDiscreteUpdates: Cannot flush updates when React is already rendering.`. The hook returned by `usePlaidIdv` likely enqueues state updates or DOM work immediately, so invoking it synchronously from the render body violates React’s rule that renders must stay pure.

Move the side effect into `useEffect` (or trigger it from the button’s `onClick`) so it runs after the component commits:

```tsx
function PlaidFormTrigger(...) {
  useEffect(() => {
    openPlaidIdvLink();
  }, [openPlaidIdvLink]);

  return null;
}
```

or avoid rendering `PlaidFormTrigger` altogether and just call `openPlaidIdvLink` from the button handler after you’ve set `isLaunched`. This prevents state updates during render and removes the warning.

